<h2>Help / FAQ</h2>
<details open>
  <summary>What is Obol?</summary>
  <p>Obol tracks per-game RP tokens. Moderators (or configured roles) can grant/remove/set balances for players.</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>Who can use the web panel?</summary>
  <p>Anyone who logs in with Discord and has <code class="mono">MANAGE_GUILD</code> or <code class="mono">ADMINISTRATOR</code> in a server.</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>How do I set the log channel?</summary>
  <p>On a serverâ€™s page, enter a channel ID in the "Log channel" field for a game. Leave blank or set <code class="mono">null</code> to disable.</p>
</details>
<details>
  <summary>Where do token permissions come from?</summary>
  <p>Same as the bot: per-game <code class="mono">grantRoleIds</code>/<code class="mono">managerRoleIds</code> plus global bot admin role IDs. The web panel checks your guild roles via the bot.</p>
</details>
